    <section id="game-introduction">
        <h2>Game Introduction</h2>
        <img style="width:30%" src="~/Content/image/pokemonred.jpg" alt="" />
        <p>Pokemon Red Leaf Green is a Game Boy Advance role-playing game developed by Game Freak, which is a part of the third generation of the Pokemon series and a remake of Pokemon Red Green, released on January 29, 2004.</p>
        <p>As in the original Pokemon Red & Green, players will control the protagonist to play from a bird's-eye view and engage in turn-based combat. The difference is that players can choose the new heroine leaf to play in this work, and the new characteristics, attributes, carrying items, moves and other systems of the second and third generations are also reflected in the game, and there is also a new Seven Islands plot for players to play.</p>
        <p>According to VGChartz, as of March 2013, the game had sold about 12 million copies worldwide (including about 3.15 million copies in Japan).</p>

